According to gov.uk guidance on approved education for Child Benefit purposes, for a young person aged 16-19, the education must be **full-time**, which means more than **12 hours per week** of supervised study or course-related work experience.

Since John's course only involves 6 hours per week, it does **not** qualify as full-time approved education. Therefore, Child Benefit cannot be claimed for him after age 16.

